# Commit And Push Preference

- When a task is complete and no further manual user action is required, create a git commit and push it by default.
- Follow the repository's existing commit message style.
- Still respect explicit user instructions to avoid committing or pushing.
- Do not auto-push if the work is incomplete, depends on pending manual validation, or would be unsafe.
